## Feature Request

### Summary
Add [Exa.ai](https://exa.ai) as a native `web_search` provider alongside the existing Brave, Gemini, Grok, Kimi, and Perplexity providers.

### Motivation
- Exa provides **AI-native semantic search** that returns highly relevant results for technical and research queries
- It offers a generous free tier (1,000 requests/month)
- Exa's neural search is fundamentally different from traditional keyword search — it understands meaning, not just keywords
- Particularly useful for developers and researchers who need precise, context-aware search results
- Already has an [official MCP server](https://mcp.exa.ai), showing strong AI-agent ecosystem alignment

### Proposed Configuration

```json5
{
  tools: {
    web: {
      search: {
        provider: "exa",
        exa: {
          apiKey: "EXA_API_KEY_HERE",
        },
      },
    },
  },
}
```

Or via environment variable: `EXA_API_KEY`

### Exa API Reference
- Docs: https://docs.exa.ai
- API: REST-based, returns structured results with titles, URLs, snippets, and optional full-text content
- Supports: semantic search, keyword search, auto mode, date filtering, domain filtering, content extraction

### Additional Context
Currently using OpenClaw with Bedrock (Claude) on AWS. The `web_search` tool defaults to Brave but we don't have a Brave API key configured. Exa's semantic search would be a great fit for AI-agent workflows.

Would also be useful for auto-detection order alongside existing providers.

Replaces the Google Gemini SDK with Groq across the bot, switching to Groq's OpenAI-compatible chat completions API with `llama3-8b-8192` as the default model.

## Changes

- **`package.json`** — swaps `@google/generative-ai` for `groq-sdk`; updates description/keywords
- **`src/agent.js`** — full rewrite of the agent loop using `groq.chat.completions.create()` with OpenAI-style message history and `tool_calls` handling; env vars renamed to `GROQ_API_KEY` / `GROQ_MODEL`
- **`src/tools/index.js`** — renames `getFunctionDeclarations()` → `getToolDefinitions()`; output format changed from Gemini's function declaration schema to OpenAI-compatible `{ type: "function", function: { ... } }` objects
- **`.env.example`** — replaces `GEMINI_API_KEY`/`GEMINI_MODEL` with `GROQ_API_KEY`/`GROQ_MODEL` pointing to `https://console.groq.com/keys`
- **`README.md`** — all Gemini references replaced with Groq; Step 3 updated with Groq key setup instructions and updated env var table

## Tool call loop (before → after)

```js
// Before: Gemini chat session with functionDeclarations
const chat = model.startChat({ history });
response = await chat.sendMessage(functionResponseParts);

// After: stateless Groq completions with OpenAI-style tool_calls
const response = await groq.chat.completions.create({
  model: GROQ_MODEL,
  messages,                  // full history including system prompt
  tools: getToolDefinitions(),
  tool_choice: "auto",
});
// tool results pushed back as { role: "tool", tool_call_id, content }
```

